==English==
===Etymology===
The term arose from attempts in the late 1800's to make
a balloon steerable.  In French, "dirigeable" means steerable.
Over time the phrase "dirigible balloon" was shortened
to just dirigible.  

In modern parlance, the term has been replaced by airship.

